===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|game|lang=enm}}, {{term|gamen|lang=enm}}, {{term|gammen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|gamen||sport, joy, mirth, pastime, game, amusement, pleasure|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|gamanan|amusement, pleasure, game", literally "participation, communion, people together|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|title=|ga-|pos=collective prefix|lang=en}} + {{proto|Germanic|title=|mann-|man|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|gamen||joy, amusement, fun, pleasure|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|gamman||mirth, rejoicing, merriment|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|gaman||fun|lang=is}}. Related to {{l|en|gammon}}, {{l|en|gamble}}.

